This wasnâ€™t too bad, but I originally used a dplyr::case_when instead of my if...else chain and because dplyr::case_when is vectorized, that wouldnâ€™t work. However, when I swapped to my if...else chain, I accidentally marked three of a kind as the same value as a full house. Quite annoying, but an easy fix.
rank &lt;- c('A', 'K', 'Q', 'J', 'T', 9:2) |&gt; rev()
