I hate when thereâ€™s a fancy math way. Itâ€™s just least common multiples this time and Iâ€™m super dumb for not thinking of this sooner. I did have to be careful with match instead of %in% because that would return the indices in the incorrect order and cause everything to fail.

start &lt;- function(end, dir) {
